ty. With new insights on the scope of private medicine and the workings of the means test in the hospital, as well as the civic, consumer and charitable meanings associated with paying the hospital, Gosling offers a fresh perspective on healthcare before the NHS and welfare before the welfare state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMedical care, Cost of. 0aMedicine (General). 0aSocial medicinezGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial medicine. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aBristol.  aBritish healthcare.  aBritish hospitals.  aCommercial Medicine.  aHealthcare.  aHospitals.  aMedical Charity.  aNHS.  aNational Health Service.  aPayment.  aPhilanthropy.  acharity.  aclass relations.  amiddle-class patients.  apayment systems.  aphilanthropy.  apolitical strategies.  apublic services.  asick poor.  avoluntary sector.1 aGosling, George Campbell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526114358zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526114358zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526114358/original  a978-3-11-128281-7 Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA